As Engrossed: S4/1/25 HB1803
1 (C) Ten Commandments Monument Display Act under § 22-3-
2 221;
3 (D) Gold Star Family Memorial Monument Fund;
4 (E) Arkansas Fallen Firefighters Memorial Board under §
5 22-3-1704; and
6 (F) Hoxie: The First Stand Memorial Monument Fund.; and
7 (G) Maurice Lee "Footsie" Britt Memorial Bust Fund.
8
9 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code Title 19, Chapter 5, Subchapter 11, is
10 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
11 19-5-1162. Maurice Lee "Footsie" Britt Memorial Bust Fund.
12 (a) There is established on the books of the Treasurer of State, the
13 Auditor of State, and the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State a trust fund to
14 be known as the "Maurice Lee "Footsie" Britt Memorial Bust Fund".
15 (b) The fund shall consist of gifts, grants, and donations from
16 individuals and organizations as provided under the Maurice Lee "Footsie"
17 Britt Memorial Bust Act, § 22-3-225, and other funds as may be provided by
18 law.
19 (c) The fund shall be used exclusively for the purpose of erecting and
20 maintaining a suitable monument on the State Capitol grounds in recognition
21 and honor of Maurice Lee "Footsie" Britt, as provided in the Maurice Lee
22 "Footsie" Britt Memorial Bust Act, § 22-3-225.
23
24 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code Title 22, Chapter 3, Subchapter 2, is amended
25 to add an additional section to read as follows:
26 22-3-225. Maurice Lee “Footsie” Britt Memorial Bust.
27 (a) This section shall be known and may be cited as the “Maurice Lee
28 “Footsie” Britt Memorial Bust Act.”
29 (b)(1) The Secretary of State shall permit and arrange for the
30 placement in the State Capitol of a memorial bust commemorating the courage,
31 honor, and sacrifice of Maurice Lee "Footsie" Britt both in war and in life.
32 (2) The bust shall be placed on the second floor of the State
33 Capitol Building in proximity to the existing bust of Winthrop Rockefeller.
34 (3)(A) The bust shall be designed and sculpted in a manner
35 similar to the existing busts located in the State Capitol Building.
36 (B) The Secretary of State, through consultation with the
2 04-01-2025 10:30:41 LGL148

